Grant Thornton Targets $200 Million African Revenue, Defi Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-05-11T06:44:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/grant-thornton-targets-200-million-african-revenue-defi-says.html
Grant Thornton  International plans to
boost revenue from  Africa  to $200 million by 2015, Le Defi
Quotidien reported, citing  Chairman Peter Bodin .  The accountancy firm currently earns revenue of about $70
million a year from the 14 African nations in which it operates,
the  Port Louis , Mauritius-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  